<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-11T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-11T10:00:00-05:00" n="1079" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1079">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00/1329: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-11T09:00:00-06:00">May 11,
                                    1944—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 12:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>159. It is probable that upon official announcement that General Martínez
                            has left the country the general strike will be immediately discontinued
                            and that this will be followed by the resumption of normal and orderly
                            life throughout the republic.</p>
                        <p>I would accordingly recommend that when I have reported the receipt of
                            official advice of the constitution of the Menéndez provisional
                            government I be instructed to establish full relations with it.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>